TI  == transferable tet m in fusobacterium nucleatum.
AB  == two tetracycline-resistant fusobacterium nucleatum strains were able to transfer, by conjugation, tetracycline resistance and the tet m determinant to recipient f. nucleatum, peptostreptococcus anaerobius, and enterococcus faecalis strains at a  frequency of 10(-1) to 10(-8).
